parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cradle/subframe due to rust and corrosion can cause the engine to fall out of the vehicle, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rattling or squealing noise
vibration
shaking
or shimmying of the vehicle
especially when driving at high speeds; visible rust or corrosion on the engine cradle/subframe; engine or transmission separation from the subframe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control module can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or shift erratically, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission slips or hesitates
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle may not shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump module can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the fuel gauge malfunctions
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine light illuminates
the engine makes unusual noises
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power train control module can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or shift erratically, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission slips or hesitates
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle may not shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cradle can cause the engine to fall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine cradle is rusting
holes are forming in the cradle
and the engine is making unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to stop properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the subframe/engine cradle can cause the engine to fall out of the vehicle, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rusted or corroded subframe/engine cradle
holes or cracks in the frame
engine mounts are bad
vehicle shakes or vibrates
difficulty steering
uneven tire wear.
